          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2015-12-22 13:44:45" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>= a kind of vest or shirt covering the upper part of the body and made of several hundred small bronze scales or platelets overlapping each other and sewn on a cloth or leather base; the scales were thin and about 11 by 6 centimeters; such armor was lighter than a solid metal breastplate and was also more flexible, giving greater maneuverability; used especially by soldiers who could not carry a shield but still needed protection in battle (for example, a chariot driver).</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>coat of mail</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
